available: arch != "x86_32"
synopsis: "Helpers for periodically yielding control to Async during long synchronous tasks"
description: "
Yield_timer is a single-module library that makes it easier for functions
performing long synchronous tasks to behave nicely with Async, by providing
an easy way to periodically call a [yield] function within some iterator.

A [Yield_timer.t] is configured with a [yield_every] span and a [yield]
function (defaulting to [Scheduler.yield]), and offers primitives such as
[yield_if_its_time] and [repeat_until_finished] that only yield when enough
time has passed since the last yield.

Convenience helpers are provided for iterating over [Sequence.t], [Map.t],
[Set.t], [List.t], and [Pipe.t] (folds, iters, maps, filters, etc.) that
transparently interleave yields at the configured cadence.
"

